      "writtenOn": "2020-04-02T21:59:02Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Where we have a few different things with similar names and similar concepts (id exception, objc_exception* exc, _cxa_exception* exception_header), the names should go well together and should be unambiguous. (And, per style, we shouldn’t abbreviate.)\n\nThe natural name for exc would be objc_exception, but that’s the type name. So how about exception_objc?",
      "revId": "bbdc8f8d02f4214e63c6bb0636364530159b3083",
